Package com.telenav.kivakit.filesystem.spi

Interface FileSystemObjectService

All Superinterfaces:
com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.Broadcaster, com.telenav.kivakit.core.value.count.ByteSized, com.telenav.kivakit.core.time.CreatedAt, Deletable, com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.Listener, com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.MessageTransceiver, com.telenav.kivakit.core.time.Modifiable, com.telenav.kivakit.core.time.ModifiedAt, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.Nameable, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.naming.NamedObject, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.messaging.Receiver, com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.Repeater, ResourcePathed, com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.Transceiver, com.telenav.kivakit.interfaces.messaging.Transmitter, UriIdentified
All Known Subinterfaces:

LocalFile, LocalFolder
public interface FileSystemObjectService extends com.telenav.kivakit.core.messaging.Repeater, com.telenav.kivakit.core.value.count.ByteSized, com.telenav.kivakit.core.time.ModifiedAt, com.telenav.kivakit.core.time.CreatedAt, com.telenav.kivakit.core.time.Modifiable, ResourcePathed, Deletable
A service provider interface (SPI) common to all filesystem objects. Implementers must provide:
  • chmod(PosixFilePermission...) - Changes permissions of the object
  • exists() - True if the object exists
  • Deletable.delete() - Deletes the object
  • isFolder() - Returns true if the object is a folder
  • parentService() - The parent FolderService of the object, if any
  • path() - The path to the object on the filesystem
  • root() - The root folder
Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
